<p>Gerald Ford, the 38th president of the United States, was born on 7/14/1913, in Omaha, Nebraska. He was 61 when he took office on 8/9/1974. Member: Republican Party.

	
		He left office on 1/20/1977.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Lawyer.
	His college: Michigan.

	
		He died in Rancho Mirage, California, on 12/26/2006.
	
</p>

